    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "results_lessons",
      "x": 100, "y": 1545,
      "width": 900, "height": 130,
      "text": "What worked                              What was hard\n─────────                                ─────────\n• Resemblyzer: stable from short audio   • Keeping inference under 8 ms per chunk\n• Streaming state: seamless output       • Safe state resets on speaker switch\n• Vosk in separate process: clean path   • Thread-safe control in realtime pipeline\n\nCore takeaway: The contribution is not TFGridNet itself — it's the full interactive system:\nenrollment, streaming inference, safe mode transitions, and realtime engineering.",
